---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Overview">
  <span class="page-tag">Planning Document</span>
  <h1>Tiny House on Trailer</h1>
  <p class="lead">Self-built with contractor friend. Low-toxicity, low embodied carbon, high efficiency.</p>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table class="kv">
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Trailer</td><td>28' &times; 8'6" purpose-built, galvanized belly pan. May revise to 26'.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Build</td><td>Self-built with contractor friend</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Goals</td><td>Low-toxicity, low embodied carbon, high efficiency</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Electrical</td><td>50A inlet plug — grid-ready, solar/microgrid compatible. Ground-mounted solar + battery bank in outbuilding. Shared microgrid possible.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Possible Locations</h2>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Region</th><th>Climate</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Western NC</strong></td><td>Zone 5A/6A — mountains, ~38" rain/yr</td><td>Marshall area. Mild summers, moderate winters. Rainwater-friendly state (no restrictions).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Upstate NY</strong></td><td>Zone 5A/5B — ~56" rain/yr</td><td>Woodstock / Hudson Valley area. Colder winters, more precipitation. Check Ulster County regs for potable rainwater.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>NE Ohio</strong></td><td>Zone 5B/6A — ~38" rain/yr</td><td>Lake effect snow in some areas. Verify local tiny house zoning and rainwater regulations.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p>House is designed to be relocatable — the trailer, modular porch, and ground-mounted solar are all site-independent. Climate design targets the coldest likely location.</p>

  <blockquote>
    <p><strong>Design reference:</strong> Rosie &amp; Caleb's DIY tiny house, Tasmania — <a href="https://www.livingbiginatinyhouse.com/episodes/this-tiny-home-is-part-of-something-much-bigger/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Living Big in a Tiny House</a>. White VJ board walls, exposed timber beams, timber slab counters, brass fixtures, reclaimed windows, patterned terracotta bathroom tile. Feeling over function.</p>
  </blockquote>

  <h2>Sections</h2>

  <div class="nav-cards">
    <a href={`${base}layout/`} class="nav-card">
      <h3>Layout</h3>
      <p>Main floor zones, bathroom, kitchen, living area, and covered porch.</p>
    </a>
    <a href={`${base}loft/`} class="nav-card">
      <h3>Bedroom Loft</h3>
      <p>King bed platform, storage, skylights, and height calculations.</p>
    </a>
    <a href={`${base}appliances/`} class="nav-card">
      <h3>Appliances &amp; Systems</h3>
      <p>Kitchen, heating, hot water, bathroom fixtures, and dining.</p>
    </a>
    <a href={`${base}envelope/`} class="nav-card">
      <h3>Building Envelope</h3>
      <p>Walls, insulation, roof, siding, and interior finishes.</p>
    </a>
    <a href={`${base}rainwater/`} class="nav-card">
      <h3>Rainwater Catchment</h3>
      <p>Collection, storage, filtration, and annual capture estimates.</p>
    </a>
    <a href={`${base}electrical/`} class="nav-card">
      <h3>Electrical &amp; Solar</h3>
      <p>House circuits, solar array, battery options, and inverter comparison.</p>
    </a>
    <a href={`${base}open-questions/`} class="nav-card">
      <h3>Open Questions</h3>
      <p>Unresolved decisions on trailer length, stove, siding, and more.</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="page-nav">
    <span></span>
    <a href={`${base}layout/`} class="next">Layout &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</Layout>
